  "article": "In a world where technology has permeated every aspect of our lives, the concept of 'fate' has taken on a new, unsettling dimension. As we stand on the precipice of the age of AI-arranged marriages, the renowned writer Van Badham raises a clarion call, urging us to reconsider the implications of handing over the reins of our most intimate relationships to algorithms.

