'When we entrust our love lives to the cold, calculating logic of algorithms, we risk losing the very essence of what makes us human,' Badham writes. 'The serendipity, the spontaneity, the messy, unpredictable journey of finding a partner – all of it is being replaced by a clinical, data-driven process that promises efficiency but robs us of our agency.'

