Ultimately, the decision on whether to legalize assisted dying in Wales will have far-reaching implications, both for individuals facing terminal illness and for the broader healthcare system. As the debate unfolds, it will be crucial to balance concerns about patient autonomy and dignity with robust safeguards to protect the vulnerable.

