  "article": "The Royal Artillery is facing a growing backlash after denying access to a valuable Asante treasure that was looted during the colonial era. The artifact, a ceremonial gold-plated sword, is part of the Asante Kingdom's cultural heritage and has been held by the Royal Artillery for decades.

