The Asante Kingdom, located in modern-day Ghana, was a powerful West African empire that resisted British colonial expansion in the 19th century. During the Anglo-Asante Wars, British forces looted numerous artifacts and cultural treasures, including the ceremonial sword now held by the Royal Artillery.

\"This sword is a symbol of our cultural identity and our history of resistance against colonial oppression,\" said Nana Agyeman Badu II, the Asantehene (King) of the Asante Kingdom. \"Its continued possession by the Royal Artillery is a painful reminder of the injustices of the past, and we demand its immediate repatriation.\"

