\"It's been a really tough few months,\" said Sarah Wilkins, a local business owner in Manchester. \"The constant rain has taken a toll on all of us, both personally and professionally. We're all just grateful to finally see some drier and milder weather.\"

Meteorologists attribute the change in weather to a shift in the jet stream, which has moved further north, allowing for a more stable high-pressure system to take hold over the UK. This has resulted in a significant drop in rainfall and a gradual increase in temperatures, providing a much-needed respite from the dreary conditions.

\"The weather we're experiencing now is a stark contrast to the start of the year,\" said John Harrington, a meteorologist at the Met Office. \"While we can't say for certain how long this milder period will last, it's certainly a welcome change after the relentless rain.\"

