The EU's '3C' Warning: A Looming Catastrophe

The European Union's latest climate report paints a grim picture of the future, projecting a potential global temperature increase of 3 degrees Celsius (5.4 degrees Fahrenheit) by the end of the century. This scenario, if realized, would have catastrophic consequences, including rising sea levels, more frequent and intense natural disasters, and widespread ecosystem collapse.

