The decision to exit TV manufacturing is a strategic move by Panasonic to focus on its core business areas, which include automotive systems, industrial equipment, and consumer electronics. The company will now rely on third-party manufacturers to produce televisions under the Panasonic brand, allowing it to leverage its brand recognition and expertise in display technology without the burden of maintaining its own production facilities.

This move is not entirely unexpected, as Panasonic had already scaled back its TV production in recent years. The company's last plasma TV factory closed in 2014, and it has since been gradually reducing its presence in the TV market. The announcement of its exit from TV manufacturing is the final chapter in Panasonic's storied history as a television manufacturer.

