In the latest round of testing, Nissan's crossover equipped with the E-Power system achieved an average of 50 miles per gallon, a figure that is typically associated with compact sedans and hatchbacks, not larger, more spacious crossover models. This breakthrough performance is a testament to the engineering prowess of Nissan's development team, who have managed to extract remarkable efficiency from a vehicle segment that has traditionally been known for its thirsty fuel consumption.

